properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 10:10AM CST until February 17 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...PRECIPITATION DELAYED A FEW HOURS...

.A Winter Weather Advisory has been extended until 3 PM for parts
of south central Minnesota. The advisory has been extended until 9
PM for Freeborn, Steele, Goodhue counties in Minnesota, and for
Pepin and Eau Claire counties in Wisconsin. The advisory is based
on snowfall amounts of one to three inches, and some light ice
accumulations. The main threat for ice is this morning, and the
main threat for snow is for this afternoon, and into the early
evening.

Precipitation has started in southwest Minnesota, and will begin
to spread across south central Minnesota before noon. Slowly, the
precipitation will expand northeast across southeast Minnesota,
and into west central Wisconsin during the afternoon, and early
evening. Some freezing rain or freezing drizzle is possible
during the morning and early afternoon. The freezing
precipitation will mix with, and change over to snow during the
afternoon. The snow will end early this evening.

* WHAT...Wet snow. Some freezing rain possible this morning with
a light glaze possible. Snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches.

* WHERE...Portions of south central Minnesota.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
